Nlg.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/format:webp/1*-y6u2xGxx83Vh4rRpOSNlg.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/format:webp/1*-y6u2xGxx83Vh4rRpOSNlg.png 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" type="image/webp"/><source data-testid="og" srcSet="https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:640/1*-y6u2xGxx83Vh4rRpOSNlg.png 640w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:720/1*-y6u2xGxx83Vh4rRpOSNlg.png 720w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:750/1*-y6u2xGxx83Vh4rRpOSNlg.png 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*-y6u2xGxx83Vh4rRpOSNlg.png 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*-y6u2xGxx83Vh4rRpOSNlg.png 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*-y6u2xGxx83Vh4rRpOSNlg.png 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*-y6u2xGxx83Vh4rRpOSNlg.png 1400w" sizes="(min-resolution: 4dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 4) and (max-width: 700px) 50vw, (min-resolution: 3dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 67vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 3) and (max-width: 700px) 65vw, (min-resolution: 2.5dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2.5) and (max-width: 700px) 80vw, (min-resolution: 2dppx) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, (-webkit-min-device-pixel-ratio: 2) and (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"/><img alt="" class="bd go pi c" width="700" height="467" loading="eager" role="presentation"/></picture></div></div><figcaption class="pj fj pk ov ow pl pm bb b bc u dy">AI-generated illustration</figcaption></figure><p id="7ce0" class="pw-post-body-paragraph pn po ji pp b kc pq pr ps kf pt pu pv he pw px py hh pz qa qb hk qc qd qe qf ig bg">I ran the benchmarks on a Tuesday afternoon. Three weeks into the evaluation, we’d pushed 847 concurrent requests through both implementations. Rust’s p99 latency came in 23% lower. Memory usage was cleaner. The compiler had caught four categories of bugs our Go tests hadn’t. I stared at the numbers for longer than I should’ve admitted in a meeting. Then I closed the tab and went back to writing more Go.</p><p id="d566" class="pw-post-body-paragraph pn po ji pp b kc pq pr ps kf pt pu pv he pw px py hh pz qa qb hk qc qd qe qf ig bg">That was eight months ago. I still think about it occasionally — not with regret exactly, but with the specific discomfort of someone who made a reasonable decision they can’t fully defend.</p><h3 id="c58a" class="qg qh ji bb qi ha qj ec hb hc qk ee hd he ql hf hg hh qm hi hj hk qn hl hm qo bg">What Rust Actually Does Better</h3><p id="7085" class="pw-post-body-paragraph pn po ji pp b kc qp pr ps kf qq pu pv he qr px py hh qs qa qb hk qt qd qe qf ig bg">The memory model. The borrow checker. A type system with sophistication our codebase never fully demanded. Rust won on paper by a distance I couldn’t argue with. But paper doesn’t deploy services.</p><p id="4a60" class="pw-post-body-paragraph pn po ji pp b kc pq pr ps kf pt pu pv he pw px py hh pz qa qb hk qc qd qe qf ig bg">Three specific things stood out during the evaluation:</p><p id="9305" class="pw-post-body-paragraph pn po ji pp b kc pq pr ps kf pt pu pv he pw px py hh pz qa qb hk qc qd qe qf ig bg"><strong class="pp jj">Memory safety without runtime overhead.</strong> Go’s garbage collector is genuinely good — better than it was in 2017, better than most teams give it credit for. But it’s still a runtime cost that appears at inopportune moments, sometimes under…</p></div></div></div></div></section></div></div></article></div><div class="e"></div><footer class="qu 